# Background:

## Mission Statement: 

**Rankhwa** helps users discover, organize, and rate manhwa/webtoons. Through community contributions, the platform refines and expands its database to improve discovery and accuracy for all readers.

## Top 5 Features:

1) Search and filter manhwa  
   1) By title, rating (1-10), release date  
   2) Later: genre/tags, popularity (\# of votes), studio  
2) User authentication  
   1) Email/pass \+ Google OAuth  
   2) Persist user ratings and lists  
3) Rate manhwa (1-10)  
   1) Rate titles; update global average  
   2) (user-specific ratings stored separately)  
4) Create and manage lists  
   1) Users can group manhwa into custom lists (e.g., “Reading”, “Completed”, “Favorites”, etc.)  
5) Submit missing manhwa  
   1) Users can contribute metadata for titles not in db, subject to approval

# Backend

## Tech Stack

* Java Spring Boot  
* Data Persistence: Spring Data JPA with Hibernate  
* DB: PostgreSQL  
* Security: Spring Security 6+ (JWT and OAuth2)  
* Maven  
* API Spec: OpenAPI (via SpringDoc) for automated documentation

## Endpoints

* Authentication (/api/auth)  
  * POST /api/auth/register  
    * Registers a new user with email/password  
    * Request Body: {username, email, password}  
    * Response: 201 Created with user data and JWT  
  * POST /api/auth/login  
    * Authenticates a user and returns a JWT  
    * Request Body: {email, password}  
    * Response: 200 OK with user data and JWT  
  * GET /oauth2/authorization/google AND /login/oauth2/code/google  
    * Endpoints managed by Spring Security for Google OAuth2  
* Manhwa (/api/manhwa)  
  * GET /api/manhwa  
    * Search page, including filtering and querying  
    * Query Params: query, min\_rating, year, sort\_by, page  
  * GET /api/manhwa/homepage  
    * Page for homepage specifically, to optimize loading  
    * Response: 200 OK with object (trending, popularThisYear, allTimePopular)  
  * GET /api/manhwa/{id}  
    * Return data for single manhwa  
    * Response: 200 OK with manhwa metadata (average rating, vote count, description)  
  * POST /api/manhwa/submit  
    * Allows authenticated users to submit a new manhwa for review  
    * Authorization: user must be logged in  
    * Request Body: title, synopsis, coverImage, genres  
    * Response: 202 Accepted, submission pending approval  
* Ratings (/api/manhwa/{id}/ratings)  
  * POST /api/manhwa/{manhwaId}/ratings  
    * Allows user to rate manhwa; update user rating and update manhwa global average rating  
    * Authorization: must be logged in  
    * Request Body: rating/score  
    * Response: 200 OK with successful rate (updated global rating)  
* User Profile and Lists (/api/users/{userId})  
  * GET /api/users/{userId}/lists  
    * Fetch all lists for user  
    * Response: 200 OK with correct structure (list\_name, items, …)  
  * POST /api/users/{userId}/lists  
    * Create a new custom list for user  
    * Authorization: must be logged in  
    * Request Body: listName  
    * Response: 201 created  
  * POST /api/users/{listId}/manhwa  
    * Adds a manhwa to a user’s list  
    * Authorization: must be logged in  
    * Request Body: manhwaId  
    * Response: 200 OK

## Database Schema

* ### Table: users

  * Stores user information for authentication and profile management  
  * ![][image8]

* ### Table: manhwa

  * Central table for all manhwa titles  
  * ![][image9]

* ### Table: ratings

  * Stores individual user ratings for each manhwa (joins users and manhwa)  
  * ![][image10]

* ### Table: user\_lists

  * Allows users to create and name custom lists  
  * ![][image11]

* ### Table: list\_items (many-to-many join table)

  * Connects manhwa titles to user lists  
  * ![][image12]

### At a high level

* Com.rankhwa.controller: Contains RestControllers for API endpoints  
* Com.rankhwa.service: business logic  
  * AuthService \- logging in  
  * JwtService \- generate and validate JWTs  
  * ManhwaService \- search, calculate, fetch homepage  
  * RatingService \- add/update user rating  
* Com.rankhwa.repository \- Spring Data JPA interfaces for db operations  
* Com.rankhwa.model \- database entities  
* Com.rankhwa.dto: for DTOs  
* Com.rankhwa.config: security configuration for managing authentication rules and JWT/OAuth2 setup

## Security Plan

* ### Authentication

  * For email/password: on successful login, server makes JWT containing user ID and roles, sent to client  
  * For Google OAuth: Spring Security for redirect and token exchange. On successful authentication, backend creates user record (if DNE) and JWT, sent to client

* ### Authorization Rules

  * Public Endpoints:  
    * GET /api/manhwa/\*, POST /api/auth/\*  
  * User-Protected Endpoints  
    * POST /api/manhwa/{id}/ratings, POST /api/users/{userId}/\*   
    * Require valid JWT; users can only modify their own lists/ratings  
  * Password Storage:   
    * BCryptPasswordEncoder from Spring Security to hash user passwords before storing
